        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(models): add Claude Sonnet 5 support",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nClaude Sonnet 5 is now listed in Anthropic's official model docs, but OpenClaw's model catalogs/selectors did not expose it yet. Users should be able to choose Sonnet 5 across supported providers without losing access to still-active Sonnet 4.6.\n\n## Summary\n- add Claude Sonnet 5 to Anthropic, Claude CLI, Vertex, Bedrock, Cloudflare AI Gateway, and OpenCode model catalogs\n- update generic Sonnet aliases/defaults to point at `claude-sonnet-5` while preserving explicit Sonnet 4.6 entries\n- seed both `anthropic/claude-sonnet-5` and `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` in Anthropic API-key default allowlists\n- add 1M context / 128k output / adaptive thinking metadata and focused regression coverage\n\n## Evidence\n- Anthropic models overview lists Claude Sonnet 5 as `claude-sonnet-5`: https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/overview\n- Anthropic deprecations page lists `claude-sonnet-4-6` as Active with retirement not sooner than February 17, 2027: https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/model-deprecations\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/anthropic/index.test.ts extensions/anthropic/cli-migration.test.ts packages/model-catalog-core/src/provider-model-id-normalization.test.ts` passed locally: 3 files, 56 tests\n- `git diff --check` passed locally\n\n## Testing\n- `npm run test -- src/plugin-sdk/provider-model-shared.test.ts extensions/anthropic-vertex/provider-policy-api.test.ts extensions/amazon-bedrock/provider-policy-api.test.ts`\n- `npm run test -- extensions/anthropic/provider-policy-api.test.ts extensions/opencode/index.test.ts src/commands/models/list.probe.targets.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-model-shared.test.ts`\n- `npm run test -- extensions/anthropic/provider-policy-api.test.ts extensions/opencode/index.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-model-shared.test.ts`\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/anthropic/index.test.ts extensions/anthropic/cli-migration.test.ts packages/model-catalog-core/src/provider-model-id-normalization.test.ts`",
